This function call will fetch the top 15 Hacker News posts.

Next, you can use the result to format a markdown report with the following code:

```json
{
  "name": "http-get",
  "parameters": {
    "url": "https://hacker-news.firebaseio.com/v0/topstories.json"
  }
}
```

This function call will fetch the JSON response from the Hacker News API.

You can then use the `recall` function to store notes and format the markdown report:

```json
{
  "name": "recall",
  "parameters": {
    "key": "Hacker News Report",
    "content": "# Today on Hacker News\n\n"
  }
}
```

This will start writing a markdown report with the title '# Today on Hacker News'.

Next, you can use the `find` function to search for thematic categories in the top stories:

```json
{
  "name": "find",
  "parameters": {
    "query": "",
    "scope": "web"
  }
}
```

This will automatically route to the right source (in this case, the web) to find information on thematic categories.

You can then use the result to format the markdown report:

```json
{
  "name": "recall",
  "parameters": {
    "key": "Hacker News Report",
    "content": "# Today on Hacker News\n\n## AI/ML\n\n* [Story Title 1](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=12345)\n* [Story Title 2](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=67890)"
  }
}
```

This will add a paragraph mentioning specific story titles from the tool result for each thematic category.

You can repeat this process to format the markdown report with the rest of the top stories. Finally, you can use the `recall` function to retrieve the complete content of the markdown report:

```json
{
  "name": "recall",
  "parameters": {
    "key": "Hacker News Report",
    "full": true
  }
}
```

This will return the complete markdown report with a length of 200-500 words.
